      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">36.215</ph> Special procedure for cost-reimbursement contracts for construction.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <p id="d2318e8" class="- topic/p ">Contracting officers may use a cost-reimbursement contract to acquire construction only when its use is consistent with <xref href="Subpart_16.3.dita#FAR_Subpart_16_3"
                  base="i1104629"
                  outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                  class="- topic/xref ">subpart  16.3</xref> and <xref href="Part_15.dita#FAR_Part_15"
                  base="i1109360"
                  outputclass="fm:Part"
                  class="- topic/xref ">part  15</xref> (see <xref href="15.404-4.dita#FAR_15_404_4"
                  base="i1106321"
                  outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                  class="- topic/xref ">15.404-4</xref>(c)(4)(i) for fee limitation on cost-reimbursement contracts).</p>
